label: Utopia, armarium codicum bibliophilorum, Cod. 106

metadata.label: Summary (English)
metadata.value: A latin book of hours with calendar, containing a selection of saints for Paris as well as several French prayers. At the end of the book, there are tables for the changing holidays beginning with the year 1640; thus it can be assumed that the manuscript was completet around this time. The majority of the miniatures are by the Master of Coëtivy, who presumably also created all compositions and thus also the preliminary drawings. The hand of a second illuminator, who can be identified as the Master of Dreux Budé, is found in the faces of Mary in the image of the birth of Jesus (f. 83v), the Adoration of the Magi (f. 92v) and the Coronation of the Virgin (f. 107r).

metadata.label: Persons
metadata.value: Illuminator: Coëtivy-Meister; Illuminator: Maître de Dreux Budé
